Hello,

You will need to have the FetchFTP processor in your fetch chain. Create 
the bean like so. (A good spot for it is just after the the fetchHttp bean.)

&lt;/bean&gt;
+ &lt;bean id=&quot;fetchFtp&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.fetcher.FetchFTP&quot;&gt;
+ &lt;/bean&gt;
&lt;bean id=&quot;extractorHttp&quot; 
class=&quot;org.archive.modules.extractor.ExtractorHTTP&quot;&gt;
&lt;/bean&gt;

Then put fetchFtp in the fetch chain.

&lt;bean id=&quot;fetchProcessors&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.FetchChain&quot;&gt;
&lt;property name=&quot;processors&quot;&gt;
&lt;list&gt;
&lt;!-- ...... various processors ....... --&gt;
&lt;ref bean=&quot;fetchHttp&quot;/&gt;
+ &lt;!-- ...fetch if FTP URI... --&gt;
+ &lt;ref bean=&quot;fetchFtp&quot;/&gt;
&lt;!-- ...extract outlinks from HTTP headers... --&gt;

Hope this helps.

Noah


